Now I have all the information needed. Here's a comprehensive answer:

---

The root cause is that `Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi` 10.0 depends on **`Microsoft.OpenApi` v2.0**, which has major breaking changes. Here's what changed and how to fix each piece:

### 1. `OpenApiString` / `OpenApiAny` types removed
All `IOpenApiAny` types (`OpenApiString`, `OpenApiInteger`, etc.) are gone. Use `System.Text.Json.Nodes.JsonNode` instead.

```csharp
// ❌ OLD
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any;
param.Schema.Example = new OpenApiString("1.0");

// ✅ NEW
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
```

### 2. `OpenApiSecurityScheme.Reference` removed
Reference properties were removed from base models. Use the new `OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference` proxy type instead:

```csharp
// ❌ OLD
var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecurityScheme
{
    Reference = new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "oauth2" }
};

// ✅ NEW
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models.References;
var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2");
```

### 3. `schema.Nullable` removed
OpenAPI 3.1 uses JSON Schema's `type` array for nullability. The `Nullable` property no longer exists. `Type` is now a **flags enum** (`JsonSchemaType`):

```csharp
// ❌ OLD
property.Value.Nullable = false;

// ✅ NEW — remove the Null flag from Type
property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
```

### 4. Collections are no longer initialized by default
Properties like `Security`, `Responses`, `AnyOf`, etc. may be `null`. Initialize before use:

```csharp
operation.Responses ??= new OpenApiResponses();
operation.Security ??= new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>();
```

### Full corrected code

```csharp
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models.References;

options.AddOperationTransformer((operation, context, ct) =>
{
    var param = operation.Parameters?.FirstOrDefault(p => p.Name == "api-version");
    if (param is not null)
    {
        param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
    }

    operation.Responses ??= new OpenApiResponses();
    operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

    var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2");
    operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
    {
        new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes }
    };

    return Task.CompletedTask;
});

options.AddSchemaTransformer((schema, context, ct) =>
{
    if (schema.Properties is not null)
    {
        foreach (var property in schema.Properties)
        {
            if (schema.Required?.Contains(property.Key) != true)
                property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
        }
    }
    return Task.CompletedTask;
});
```

For more details, see the [OpenAPI.NET v2.0 upgrade guide](https://github.com/microsoft/OpenAPI.NET/blob/main/docs/upgrade-guide-2.md).
